txt.en:
'We are as ready as we shall ever be, [placeholder]. 

'If Éowyn and the rest of Kingstead stand ready, we can begin moving to Dunharrow at her command. I know not if more matters demand her attention first, but Underharrow is prepared.

'I must tend to the people here, but [placeholder], I would ask you to return to Edoras. Inform Éowyn that her people stand ready and waiting for the journey ahead.'
Through your efforts in the Harrowdale, Ellen Fremedon and the people of Kingstead stand ready to travel to Dunharrow.

'Ah, so Ellen has made ready the preparations?

'I am glad to hear such tidings. She and I have not seen eye to eye on many matters, but surely, we both see the importance of sheltering the people of Rohan from harm.

'When we have made ready here in Edoras, we can begin our journey to Dunharrow!'
Éowyn can be found outside Meduseld in Edoras.\n\nEllen Fremedon has asked you to speak to Éowyn.
